Effective Reproduction Number: Israel vs.Â OECD

Abstract

The following code estimates the effective reproduction number \(R_t\) for Israel and compares it to the distribution of other OECD countriesâ \(R_t\).

Load packages

library(tidyverse)   # for wrangling and plotting data
library(EpiEstim)    # for estimating R_t
library(lubridate)   # for handling dates
library(tidycovid19) # for downloading ECDC data
library(countrycode) # for handling country codes
library(scales)      # for dates on the x-axis
library(hrbrthemes)  # for a nice figure theme
library(zoo)         # for rolling means
library(gghighlight) # for highlighting plots
library(patchwork)   # for combining separate ggplots
library(glue)        # for pasting strings

Set parameters

data_source <- 1   # which data source to use (1=JHU 0=ECDC)
window      <- 7   # smoothing window (days)
mean_si     <- 4.5 # mean of the serial interval
std_si      <- 3.5 # standard deviation of the serial interval

Lockdown dates

events <- 
  tribble(
    ~date, ~event,
    ymd("2020-09-18"), "Lockdown start",
    ymd("2020-10-18"), "Exit phase 1",
    ymd("2020-11-01"), "Exit phase 2",
    ymd("2020-11-08"), "Exit phase 3"
  )

Read data

Download cases, tests, and population data using the {tidycovid19} package

if (data_source == 1) {
  df_jhu  <- download_jhu_csse_covid19_data(cached = FALSE)
} 
if (data_source == 0) {
  df_ecdc <- download_ecdc_covid19_data(cached = FALSE)
}

df_owid <- download_owid_testing_data(cached = TRUE) # OWID data
df_wb   <- download_wbank_data(cached = TRUE) # world bank data

Process data

Generate new cases for each country

if (data_source == 1) {
df <-
  df_jhu %>%
  mutate(cases = confirmed - lag(confirmed, 1)) %>%
  select(iso3c, date, cases)
} 
if (data_source == 0) {
df <- 
  df_ecdc %>% 
  select(iso3c, date, cases)
}

Generate new tests for each country

df_tests <- df_owid %>% 
  mutate(tests = total_tests - lag(total_tests, 1)) %>% 
  select(iso3c, date, tests)

Join dataframes

df <- 
  df %>% 
  left_join(df_tests) %>% 
  mutate(positive_rate = (cases / tests) * 100)

Filter OECD countries

A list with names of OECD countries

oecd_names <- c(
  "Israel", "Austria", "Belgium", "Czech Republic",
  "Denmark", "Estonia", "Finland", "France",
  "Germany", "Greece", "Hungary", "Iceland",
  "Ireland", "Italy", "Latvia", "Luxembourg",
  "Netherlands", "Norway", "Poland", "Portugal",
  "Slovak Republic", "Slovenia", "Spain",
  "Sweden", "Switzerland", "United Kingdom",  "Canada",
  "Chile", "Mexico", "United States", "Australia",
  "Japan", "Korea", "New Zealand", "Turkey"
)

Transform country names to iso3c codes using the {countrycode} package

oecd_iso3c <- 
  countrycode(
    oecd_names,
    origin = "country.name",
    destination = "iso3c"
  )

Filter OECD countries

df_oecd <- 
  df %>% 
  filter(iso3c %in% oecd_iso3c) %>% 
  left_join(df_wb)

Set smoothing window

Here window holds the size of the window (default is 7 days)

obs <- nrow(
  df_oecd %>% 
    filter(iso3c == "ISR", date >= ymd("2020-03-15"))
)

t_start <- seq(2, obs - window + 1) 
t_end   <- t_start + window - 1

A function that estimates \(R_t\)

We now write a simple function that extracts \(R_t\) for a given country using the {EpiEstim} package

extract_R <- function(incid, output, t_start, t_end, mean_si, std_si) {
  
  model <- 
    estimate_R(
      incid = incid, 
      method = "parametric_si",
      config = make_config(
        list(
          mean_si = mean_si,
          std_si = std_si,
          t_start = t_start,
          t_end = t_end
        )
      )
    )
  
  rep_num <- model$R[[3]]
    
  output <-cbind(output, rep_num)
  
  return(output)
}

Estimate \(R_t\) for OECD countries

Estimate \(R_t\) for each OECD country, and ignore those for which the function throws an error (probably due to data issues).

output <- c()

for (i in oecd_iso3c){

  incid <- 
    df_oecd %>%
    filter(
      date >= ymd("2020-03-15"),
      iso3c == i
    ) %>%
    select(date, cases) %>%
    rename(dates = date, I = cases)

  tryCatch(
  output <- extract_R(incid, output, t_start, t_end, mean_si, std_si),
  error = function(e) e
  )

}

Estimate \(R_t\) for Israel

Now we estimate Israel \(R_t\) and add it to the output table.

incid <- 
  df_oecd %>%
  filter(
    date >= ymd("2020-03-15"),
    iso3c == "ISR"
  ) %>%
  select(date, cases) %>%
  rename(dates = date, I = cases)

model <- 
  estimate_R(
    incid = incid, 
    method = "parametric_si",
    config = make_config(
        list(
          mean_si = mean_si,
          std_si = std_si,
          t_start = t_start,
          t_end = t_end
        )
      )
  )
  
isr_rep_num <- 
  model$R %>% 
  select(3) %>% 
  pull()
    
output <- 
  cbind(isr_rep_num, output)

Calculate median and interquartile range

\(R_t\)

Dataframe to tibble

df_R <- 
  output %>% 
  as_tibble()

Calculate the median and the interquartile range, by rows (i.e., dates)

df_R_q <- 
  df_R %>% 
  rowwise() %>% 
  mutate(
    q50    = quantile((c_across(rep_num:V29)), probs = 0.50),
    q_up   = quantile((c_across(rep_num:V29)), probs = 0.75),
    q_down = quantile((c_across(rep_num:V29)), probs = 0.25)
  ) %>%
  select(isr_rep_num, starts_with("q")) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  mutate(
    date = seq(from = ymd("2020-03-12"), by = "1 day", length.out = dim(output)[[1]])
  )

Cases

Generate 7-day rolling mean of daily cases

df_oecd_cases <- 
  df_oecd %>% 
  filter(
    population >= 1e6,
    date >= ymd("2020-03-01")
  ) %>% 
  mutate(
    cases_ma = rollmean(cases, 7, na.pad=TRUE, align="right"),
    cases_ma_pc = cases_ma / population * 1e6
  ) %>%
  select(iso3c, date, cases_ma_pc)

Calculate the median and interquartile range, by rows (i.e., dates)

df_oecd_cases_q <- 
  df_oecd_cases %>% 
  pivot_wider(date, names_from = "iso3c", values_from = "cases_ma_pc") %>% 
  rowwise() %>% 
  mutate(
    q50    = quantile((c_across(AUS:USA)), probs = 0.50, na.rm = TRUE),
    q_up   = quantile((c_across(AUS:USA)), probs = 0.75, na.rm = TRUE),
    q_down = quantile((c_across(AUS:USA)), probs = 0.25, na.rm = TRUE)
  ) %>%
  select(date, ISR, starts_with("q")) %>% 
  ungroup()

Tests

df_oecd_tests <- 
  df_oecd %>% 
  filter(
    population >= 1e6,
    date >= ymd("2020-03-01")
  ) %>% 
  mutate(
    positive_rate_ma = rollmean(positive_rate, 7, na.pad=TRUE, align="right"),
  ) %>%
  select(iso3c, date, positive_rate_ma)
df_oecd_tests_q <- 
  df_oecd_tests %>% 
  pivot_wider(date, names_from = "iso3c", values_from = "positive_rate_ma") %>% 
  rowwise() %>% 
  mutate(
    q50    = quantile((c_across(AUS:USA)), probs = 0.50, na.rm = TRUE),
    q_up   = quantile((c_across(AUS:USA)), probs = 0.75, na.rm = TRUE),
    q_down = quantile((c_across(AUS:USA)), probs = 0.25, na.rm = TRUE)
  ) %>%
  select(date, ISR, starts_with("q")) %>% 
  ungroup() %>% 
  drop_na()

plot_start <- ymd("2020-09-01")

if (data_source == 1) {

if (data_source == 0) {

\(R_t\)

Store information regarding the latest values (will be used in the plot to annotate the lines.)

last_obs <- df_R_q %>% 
  slice(dim(output)[[1]])

last_date   <- last_obs %>% pull(date)
last_oecd   <- last_obs %>% pull(q50) %>% round(2) %>% unname()
last_israel <- last_obs %>% pull(isr_rep_num) %>% round(2) %>% unname()

label_israel <- paste0("Israel\n", last_israel)
label_oecd   <- paste0("OECD\n", last_oecd)

Plot \(R_t\)

p_R <- df_R_q %>% 
  filter(
    date >= plot_start
  ) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = date, y = q50)) +
  geom_line(
    aes(x = date, y = q50, color = "OECD median"),
    size = 1,
    color = "#2d003f"
  ) +
  geom_line(
    aes(x = date, y = isr_rep_num),
    color = "#05827e",
    size = 1,
  ) +
  geom_ribbon(
    aes(ymin = q_down, ymax = q_up),
    fill = "#2d003f",
    alpha = 0.1
  ) +
  geom_hline(aes(yintercept = 1), color = "black", size = 0.5) +
  annotate("rect", fill = "#ffe612", xmin = last_date, xmax = last_date + days(10), ymin = -Inf, ymax = +Inf, alpha = 0.4) +
  geom_vline(data = events, aes(xintercept = date), linetype = 2) +
  geom_text(data = events, aes(x=date, y=0.5, label=event), size=3, angle=90, vjust=-0.4, hjust=0) +
  annotate("label", x = last_date + days(5), y = last_oecd, label = label_oecd, color = "#2d003f", size = 3.5) +
  annotate("label", x = last_date + days(5), y = last_israel, label = label_israel, color = "#05827e", size = 3.5) +
  labs(
    y = expression("R"[t]),
    x = "",
    title = "Effective Reproduction Number",
    subtitle = "Israel vs. OECD median and interquartile range",
    color = "",
    lty = "",
    caption = glue("Notes: Yellow shaded area denotes the 10-days between infection and outpatiant testing.\nData: {data_source_name}.")
  ) +
  scale_x_date(labels = date_format("%d-%m")) +
  theme(
    legend.position="top",
    plot.caption = element_text(hjust = 0)
  ) +
  ylim(0.5,1.5)

p <- p_R + p_cases +
  plot_annotation(caption = paste0("Timestamp: ", now())) &
  theme(text = element_text('mono', size = 14))

ggsave(
  filename = "plots/r-cases-oecd.png",

  scale = 2
)
